/target

# cargo-fuzz transient output (ms phase, Cycle C). The fuzz workspace's
# corpus/ and Cargo.lock ARE committed; build/artifacts/coverage are not.
# (The root `/target` above does NOT cover the nested fuzz/target, so it is
# listed explicitly here.)
fuzz/target/
fuzz/artifacts/
fuzz/coverage/

# Committed `cargo vendor` tree (reproducible-builds-musl cycle, P3b) — the
# offline reproducible build needs EVERY vendored file. ms's root-anchored
# `/target` does NOT reach into vendor/, so no vendored file is excluded today;
# this negation is a defensive guard (matching the canonical mk-codec fix) so
# that if any unanchored `**/target/`-style rule is ever added, vendored SOURCE
# files whose SHA-256 is pinned in each crate's `.cargo-checksum.json` (e.g.
# `vendor/cc/src/target/*.rs`, the cc crate's target DB — a build dep of
# secp256k1-sys) are NOT silently dropped. MUST sort AFTER any rule it negates.
!vendor/**
